### SCAI Lucky Loop — Manual API Test Requests
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension, or copy each block's
### curl-equivalent (shown in comments) into a terminal.
###
### IMPORTANT: Telegram login requires a real signed initData string from
### an actual Telegram Mini App session — you cannot fake this without the
### real bot token and a real Telegram client. For local testing without
### Telegram, see the "TESTING WITHOUT TELEGRAM" note at the bottom.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Telegram login (replace initData with a real value from your bot)
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/telegram -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"initData":"..."}'
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/telegram
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "initData": "auth_date=1750000000&user=%7B%22id%22%3A123456789%2C%22username%22%3A%22testuser%22%7D&hash=PASTE_REAL_HASH_HERE"
}

### 3. Get my profile (replace TOKEN with the token from step 2's response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/user/me
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

### 4. Get my coin balance (note: :id must match YOUR OWN user id, returned in step 3)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/user/1/coins
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

### 5. Spin for free coins
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/spin
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

### 6. Check today's ticket availability
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/today
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

### 7. Buy a ticket (only works between SALES_OPEN_HOUR and SALES_CLOSE_HOUR)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/buy-ticket
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 8. Check withdrawal eligibility
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/withdraw/eligibility
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

### 9. Request a withdrawal (requires 1000+ coins and 5+ active referrals)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/withdraw
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "walletAddress": "0x000000000000000000000000000000000000aa",
  "amountCoins": 1000
}

### 10. View a draw's public result
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/draws/2026-06-18

### 11. Verify a completed draw was fair (after it's run)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/draws/2026-06-18/verify

### ---- ADMIN ENDPOINTS (your telegram_id must be in ADMIN_TELEGRAM_IDS) ----

### 12. List all users
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

### 13. View ticket sales for a date
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/tickets/2026-06-18
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

### 14. List pending withdrawals
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/withdrawals/pending
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

### 15. Force-run today's draw (manual override / testing)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/draw/2026-06-18/run
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_TOKEN

###############################################################################
# TESTING WITHOUT A REAL TELEGRAM BOT
#
# Since step 2 needs a genuinely signed Telegram payload, the fastest way to
# test everything else locally is to temporarily bypass verification:
#
# 1. Open src/controllers/authController.js
# 2. Comment out the verification block and hardcode a fake telegramId, e.g.:
#
#      const verification = { valid: true, data: { telegramId: "999000111", username: "dev_test" } };
#      // const verification = verifyTelegramWebAppData(initData);
#      // if (!verification.valid) { throw new AppError(...) }
#
# 3. Now POST any body to /api/auth/telegram and you'll get back a real JWT.
# 4. REMOVE THIS BYPASS BEFORE DEPLOYING — it would let anyone log in as
#    any user with zero verification. This is for local dev only.
###############################################################################
